### Sprint 1 — One-Shot Architecture + Reveal Mechanic

**Goal:** Redesign how the map renders. Generate everything at once but reveal it progressively as the user explores.

- [ ] Remove click-to-expand API call from `js/main_functions.js`
- [ ] On Map button → single API call → all nodes and edges returned at once
- [ ] All nodes and edges render immediately but **grayed out and opaque** (not visible yet)
- [ ] Center/search node is fully visible and vibrant from the start
- [ ] Single click on a grayed node → node “pops alive” with full color and vibrance
- [ ] When node pops → show summary panel with node details, links, and map connections
- [ ] Connected edges to that node also pop alive when node is clicked
- [ ] Apply Fractal colors from AI response to each node (not Wikipedia depth colors)
- [ ] Grey emergent node styled distinctly — larger, different border
- [ ] Demo mode nodes labeled clearly — append `(DEMO)` to each node name so team knows immediately when backend is not connecting correctly e.g. “Domain A (DEMO)”, “Emergent Pattern (DEMO)”

